From b552fcd5b9d0d3abed2bdb0e53eef5dfbf860bdd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaron Paterson <apaterson@pm.me>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 19:40:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] odb/refs: add local helper backends for external storage

Introduce local helper backends for both object storage and ref
storage, allowing git to delegate these operations to an external
process. This follows the same pattern as remote helpers
(git-remote-*), which already handle both refs (list) and objects
(fetch/push) in a single process.

A single "git-local-<name>" binary handles both ODB and ref
operations, matching how "git-remote-<name>" handles both for
remote repositories. The local/remote naming parallel makes the
distinction clear.

The shared helper process manager (helper.c) spawns the binary
with one argument (the gitdir path) and negotiates capabilities.
Multiple helper_process structs with the same name share a single
child process via an internal cache, so the ODB and ref backends
talk to one process.

Protocol uses a flat command namespace:
  ODB: info, get, put, have, list-objects
  Refs: read, list, transaction-begin/update/create/delete/
        prepare/finish/abort, create

Configuration uses the existing URI format:
  extensions.objectStorage = helper://sqlite
  extensions.refStorage = helper://sqlite

Signed-off-by: Aaron Willoughby <aaron@omniband.org>
